Notion provides a hosted Model Context Protocol server for interactive AI use, while also offering an open-source server for programmatic or service-level needs [1][2][3].

For hosted Notion MCP, use the following endpoints with OAuth 2.0 PKCE:
- Streamable HTTP: https://mcp.notion.com/mcp
- Server-Sent Events (SSE): https://mcp.notion.com/sse

For service-level access, self-host the official open-source server (@notionhq/notion-mcp-server) using a Notion integration token [2][3]. Configure it in your MCP client settings:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "notionApi": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@notionhq/notion-mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "NOTION_TOKEN": "ntn_"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The hosted server is optimized for human-in-the-loop OAuth, whereas self-hosted versions support headless environments like CI/CD and background agents [2][3].
